  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN158.1-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻi <app><lem>cevilikkuc colluvāḷāyc colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #RK">cevilittāykkuc colluvāḷāy talaimakaṉ kēṭpac colliyatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said as one speaking to the foster mother while HE was behind the hedge.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN158.1">
              <l>urumuraṟu karuviya perumaḻai talai<supplied>i</supplied>p</l>
              <l>peyalāṉ ṟavinta tūṅkiru ṇaṭunā<supplied>ṇ</supplied></l>
              <l>miṉṉunimir<supplied>n</supplied> taṉṉa kaṉaṅkuḻai yimaippap</l>
              <l>piṉṉuviṭu neṟiyiṟ <supplied>ki</supplied>ḷai<supplied>iya</supplied> kūntalaḷ</l>
              <l>varaiyiḻi mayili ṉolkuvaṉa ḷotuṅki</l>
              <l>miṭaiyūr piḻiyak kaṇṭaṉe ṉivaḷeṉa<anchor n="1"/></l>
              <l>valaiyal vāḻivēṇ ṭaṉṉainam paṭappaic</l>
              <l>cūruṭaic cilampiṟ cuṭarppū veytu</l>
              <l>tāmvēṇ ṭuruvi <supplied>ṉa</supplied>ṇaṅkumār varumē</l>
              <l>naṉaviṉ vāyē pōlat tuñcunark</l>
              <l>kaṉavāṇṭu maruṭṭalu muṇṭē yivaṭāṉ</l>
              <l>cuṭari<del>ci</del>ṉṟu tamiyaḷum paṉikkum veruvara</l>
              <l>maṉṟa mātta kū<supplied>kai</supplied> kuḻaṟiṉu<del>m</del></l>
              <l>neñcaḻin tara<supplied>ṇa</supplied>ñ cēru mataṉṟalaip</l>
              <l>pulikkaṇat taṉṉa nāytoṭar viṭṭu</l>
              <l>muruka <supplied>ṉa</supplied>ṉṉa cīṟṟattuk kaṭuntiṟa</l>
              <l>lentaiyu milla ṉāka</l>
              <l>vañcuva ḷallaḷō vivaḷitu ceyalē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>“After rain great in amount had showered down as thunder rumbled, (1)</l>
                <l>at midnight with hanging darkness when the raining had finally ceased (2)</l>
                <l>while [her] thick earrings twinkled like flashes that shoot up, (3)</l>
                <l>stepping sideways with the movement of a peacock descending from a mountain, (5)</l>
                <l>she with tresses that branched out into curls escaping from [her] braids,</l>
                <l>I have seen her mount [and] descend from the platform”, saying [so] (6)</l>
                <l>do not slap [her], oh, please, mother. In our garden (7)</l>
                <l>there [is] a demoness coming in the shape she chooses at will, (9)</l>
                <l>reaching for the glowing flowers on the haunted mountain side, (8)</l>
                <l>and just like a true [event] in reality, there is a charm [wrought]</l>
                <l>by a dream there on those who sleep. As for her, (10f.)</l>
                <l>as she came to be frightened, shivering all alone without light, (12)</l>
                <l>even though the owl was shrieking in the mango tree on the village common, (13)</l>
                <l>she joins [me] for protection, heart desolate. On top of that, (14)</l>
                <l>as the dogs were let loose like a pack of tigers (15)</l>
                <l>[and] my father [was] in the house, (17)</l>
                <l>with the fierce power of [his] Murukaṉ-like fury, (16)</l>
                <l>would she not be afraid of doing this? (18)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

